CO: RMW, REP: Gross, CLERK: Liddle. ADA:  Alexis S. Mckinley   DF ATTY:  Jessie Gwynn Weber   DF:  Brendan Christopher Smith appeared. Case called at 8:35 a.m. ADA McKinley states there is a global resolution. Recites agreement and gives recommendations. State has complied with Victims Rights. Victim statement has been filed with the court. No requesting DE register as a sex offender. Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads NC to amended Ct 1 and added Ct. 2 Misd. Sexual Intercourse with Child age 16 or older per Statute 948.09 in 15CF274. DE sworn. Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea. Attorney's stipulate to the facts. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of amended Ct 1 and added Ct. 2 Misd. Sexual Intercourse with Child age 16 or older per Statute 948.09 in 15CF274. Sentencing arguments. Atty Weber files an assessment report with the court and is requesting it to be sealed. Court will order the report to be sealed. DE makes statement.  Crt orders:

Count 1: 

- S/W 2 years probation. Report to probation by no later than noon today

- Restitution in the amount of $1,489.75

- N/C with victim or family

- Court Costs in the amount of $243.00

- DNA Sample and DNA Surcharge $200.00

- 90 days jail stayed

-  Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times while this case is ongoing. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia.

-   Complete all other programming as deemed appropriate by the COMPAS assessment and the Department of Corrections

Count 2:

- S/W 2 years probation. Report to probation by no later than noon today. Run concurrent to Count 1

- N/C with victim or family

- Court Costs in the amount of $243.00

- DNA Sample and DNA Surcharge $200.00

- 90 days jail stayed

-  Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times while this case is ongoing. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia.

Preliminary hearing at 08-28-2015 03:00 pm

It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, A.R.S. dob 4/8/98  or the residence.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, social media including but not limited to texting, Facebook, Twitter, contact through the mail, and/or through a third person.  The aforementioned condition of bond/bail is set pursuant to Sec. 969.02(3)(d), Wis Stats.

Further, it is ORDERED that if the defendant fails to comply with the conditions of his/her bond/bail that he/she may be charged with the offense of bailjumping contrary to Sec. 946.49(1)(a), Wis. Stats.
